    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-06-29T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-06-29T08:00:00-05:00" n="862"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d862">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">660H.1115/19: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-29T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 29, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:56 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>178. Referring to my telegram No. 166, June 15, 5 p.m., the Minister of Finance
                    promises a reply within the next few days.</p>
                <p>He inquired whether it might be possible to arrange a barter transaction for raw
                    cotton against bauxite similar to the recent British-American barter of cotton
                    for rubber.<note n="20" xml:id="d862fn20">See <ref target="#pg_234">pp.
                            234</ref> ff.</note> Will the Department please telegraph its comments
                    on this proposal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
